      <section id="objective" class="card">
        <h2>Objective</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Read the structured failure artifacts from Sprint 14.</li>
          <li>Produce a deterministic first-pass diagnosis for each failed test.</li>
          <li>Point the reviewer to the right evidence first.</li>
          <li>Reduce time-to-orientation without pretending to fix the issue.</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="callout">
          <span class="tag">Rule</span>
          <p style="margin:8px 0 0;">
            The triage agent is a disciplined first responder, not an autonomous fixer.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="done" class="card">
        <h2>Definition of done</h2>
        <ul>
}</code></pre>

  return &#123;
    classification: 'UNKNOWN',
    confidence: 0.4,
    reason: 'No current deterministic rule matched.',
    recommendedNextStep: 'Inspect trace and extend taxonomy if pattern is legitimate.'
  &125;
}</code></pre>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="commands" class="card">
        <h2>Commands</h2>
        <pre><code>node scripts/triage-agent.js
cat test-results/triage/triage-report.json | jq .</code></pre>

        <div class="callout">
          <span class="tag">GitLab shape</span>
          <pre><code>triage_failures:
  stage: report
  script:
    - node scripts/triage-agent.js
    - cat test-results/triage/triage-report.json
  artifacts:
    when: always
    paths:
      - test-results/triage/</code></pre>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="expected" class="card">
        <h2>Expected outputs</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><span class="ok">✔</span> Every failed test is classified into a bounded category.</li>
          <li><span class="ok">✔</span> The report gives a reason and a next step rather than echoing raw stack text.</li>
          <li><span class="ok">✔</span> The reviewer knows which artifact to open first.</li>
          <li><span class="ok">✔</span> Unknown remains available when the rule set is incomplete.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="failures" class="card">
        <h2>Failure modes</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Triage adds no value:</strong> it only repeats raw error text. Action: summarize category, reason, next step.</li>
          <li><strong>Everything becomes TIMING:</strong> action: prioritize specific rules above generic timeout handling.</li>
          <li><strong>LLM enrichment contradicts deterministic rule:</strong> action: deterministic classification wins.</li>
          <li><strong>Bad fix suggestions:</strong> action: forbid timeout inflation, blind retries, and DOM-coupled selector drift.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="ops" class="card">
        <h2>Operational value</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Faster failure orientation in CI.</li>
          <li>Consistent first-pass diagnosis across reviewers.</li>
          <li>Clear evidence-first workflow for new hires.</li>
          <li>Foundation for future trend reporting and agent memory.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

